  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Chop the<strong> potatoes</strong> into chunky chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chunky chips </strong>to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the chips are golden and cooked through – these are your <strong>chunky chips</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661873720727-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661873720727-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661873720727-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661873720727-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661873720727-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the<strong> creamed</strong> <strong>coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped creamed coconu</strong>t and <strong>red</strong> <strong>Thai curry paste</strong> to a pot with a lid with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>soy</strong> <strong>sauce</strong>, the <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, the <strong>lime</strong> <strong>leaves</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> then bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has reduced to a thick curry-like consistency, then cover with a lid and set aside for later – this is your<strong> Thai red curry sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661873726812-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661873726812-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661873726812-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661873726812-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661873726812-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Roll the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut into quarters</p><p>Add the <strong>cornflour</strong> and 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g] </span><strong>flour</strong> to a large bowl with the <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>remaining soy sauce </strong>and the juice of 1/4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1/2] </span><strong>lime</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>the<strong> chopped coriander </strong>and 80ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[160ml]</span> <strong>very cold water </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>batter</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661873744767-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661873744767-x400.jpg",
